    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">Sweet and Sour Pork</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 pound pork tenderloin, cut into bite-sized pieces</li>
            <li>1/2 cup cornstarch</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon salt</li>
            <li>1/4 teaspoon black pepper</li>
            <li>Vegetable oil for frying</li>
            <li>1 bell pepper, cut into chunks</li>
            <li>1 onion, cut into chunks</li>
            <li>1 cup pineapple chunks (fresh or canned)</li>
            <li>1/2 cup ketchup</li>
            <li>1/4 cup rice vinegar</li>
            <li>3 tablespoons brown sugar</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon soy sauce</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon ginger, minced</li>
            <li>2 cloves garlic, minced</li>
            <li>Sesame seeds and chopped green onions for garnish</li>
            <li>Cooked white rice for serving</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Pork</li>
            <li>Asian</li>
            <li>Sweet and Sour</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a bowl, combine cornstarch, salt, and black pepper. Dredge the pork pieces in the cornstarch mixture, shaking off excess.</li>
            <li>In a large pan or wok, heat vegetable oil over medium-high heat. Fry the pork pieces until golden brown and cooked through. Remove and set aside on paper towels.</li>
            <li>In the same pan, saut√© ginger and garlic until fragrant. Add bell pepper, onion, and pineapple chunks. Cook until the vegetables are slightly tender.</li>
            <li>In a small bowl, whisk together ketchup, rice vinegar, brown sugar, and soy sauce. Pour the sauce over the vegetables in the pan.</li>
            <li>Add the fried pork pieces to the pan and toss everything together until well coated in the sweet and sour sauce.</li>
            <li>Serve the Sweet and Sour Pork over cooked white rice, garnished with sesame seeds and chopped green onions.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your flavorful Sweet and Sour Pork!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

